title: For Sale:  LUGER
postcontent:
Luger 1921 DWM in 9mm it's the last year that it was made by Deutsch Waffen und Munitions.  The last year of production of this gun 40K were made 30K were police issued in 9mm,  the rest went to the Army.  The large majority of the Army pistols were chambered in the .30 cal.    This is an Army issued model in the 9mm. It does not have the police stamping on the sides,  nor does it have the police seer on it.  All numbers match on the item and it does have several of the Nazi/ Reich stamps on it as well.  The only part of the gun that is not original is the Magazine  it dates to 1938 or 1939, this really does not effect the value of the gun itself.  
I had it looked at by several sources and it  values from $800-$1000 I took it a couple of weeks ago to the Medina gun show and talked to a several of the Luger guys there to confirm everything about it.   It is in great shape according to the dozen or so guys that looked at the item and they all  agreed that the price of $800 would be on the low end of the spectrum for the gun.  I feel the amount i'm asking for is more then fair.  do your research and you'll agree.

I'm looking to sell the item more then trade it!

I have no real desire to make a trade.  At this point i'm just not that interested in this gun.   If your looking to trade for this i'm looking at getting several items for it,  I like .22 pistols and  rugers.  
Pistols and semi auto's. chambered in 9mm,  .38  .380, 357 and 44.

 I'm not interested in .40 or .45 pistols,  one less round I would need to buy.  I have no desire to buy to trade for your personal AR creation either.

Simple pump shotguns work as well.  As well as possibly .22 rifles or 9mm rifles as well.


As the guy stated in an earlier post.  I have a price see the amount above.  I am aware of the items value.  I've looked at auctions,  I've had it looked at by all most a dozen people to confirm the value of the guy.  What i'm asking for is more then a fair price.  You can't buy a cheap beat-up Luger for under $600 these days.

title: For Sale/Trade:  SHTF AK74 package
postcontent:
Due to a miserable economy, and less-than-inspiring national and world events, I am consolodating my battery into a practical selection, and my one 5.45 caliber rifle must go.
However, I don't want to just sell someone a rifle. I want to help someone who wants to be prepared. If you have been looking into buying a firearm because the future looks uncertain, then please take a moment to consider this package.

This is an AK74 in 5.45x39, built on a bulgarian parts kit by IAC. It has wooden furniture, a CHROME LINED BARREL, as well as chrome lined gas tube and muzzle device, and an AK recoil buffer installed. 
The 5.45 is an excellent defensive cartridge, known in the middle east as the "poison bullet" for its ability to maim. It is cheap to shoot, and has extremely low recoil. Its ballistics mimic that of the american 5.56. 
It is a tack driver as well, capable of 2 MOA with irons. The scope mount on the side of the receiver could be put to very good use with a decent piece of glass.

This package includes the following
- AK74 rifle
- (9) 30rd bulgarian double circle 21 magazines
- (1) unopened crate of 5.45 ammuntion (2,160rds)
- (4) boxes of 5.45 ammuntion (120rds)
- (1) ChiCom 3 cell chest rig
- (1) rifle carrying case

I am losing 200 dollars at this price, but it is acceptable to me, if it goes to someone who needs it, and who will use it. 900 is a good price, and I cannot go any lower, and will only sell as a package.

I will consider trades for Springfield M1A rifles, or good 47 pattern AK's(I like underfolders or factory sidefolders) or RPK's. Let me know what you have, and we can discuss it. I am open to negotiate a little. 

Thank you, and god bless.
